[Hopefully, the DNR is picking up all the dead birds. To leave the dead birds to decompose is to perpetuate the situation. As the birds decompose, and maggots develop, those maggots will be filled with botulinum toxin. When another bird consumes the maggot, the cycle continues.

Botulinum toxin causes botulism. The toxin is a neurotoxic protein. The toxic protein is produced by _Clostridium botulinum_. Botulism is an extremely potent toxin, one of the most toxic agents known.

While botulism is extremely toxic, it has been used medically in treating strokes and migraines, and cosmetically in treating wrinkles, to name a few uses. There are other appropriate medical uses.

Michigan may be located on the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2691474,225. - Mod.TG]
